-- Turkey to Raise Maximum Rates on Credit Cards, Hurriyet Reports
-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 2011-12-24T12:45:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-24/turkey-to-raise-maximum-rates-on-credit-cards-hurriyet-reports.html
Turkey â€™s central bank raised the
maximum monthly interest rate on Turkish lira credit card debt
while leaving dollar- and euro-denominated borrowing costs
unchanged, Hurriyet  reported , citing the Official Gazette.  For the three-month period starting January, credit card
providers can charge as much as 2.34 percent a month on lira
borrowings, up from 2.12 percent, the Istanbul-based newspaper
said.  Interest rates  on dollar loans are capped at 1.7 percent
and euro borrowings are at 1.64 percent, Hurriyet reported.  The maximum monthly late fee on lira denominated credit
card spending will rise to 2.84 percent from 2.62 percent,
according to the newspaper. The charge is unchanged at 2.2
percent for dollar debt and 2.14 percent for euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
